verses.text:
I hear thy welcome voice, That calls on me to be true;
I long to rise and follow thee, And do what thou wilt do;
I'll go with thee through the garden, Through the judgment and the pain;
I'll come and love thee freely, And I'll love thee as I came.

I am coming to the Lord, I am coming to the Lord;
Come and let me know thy name, Though the conflict may be long;
I am coming to the Lord, I am coming to the Lord!
